	<article id="post-121" class="post-121 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-resources">
		<header class="entry-header">
						<h1 class="entry-title"><a href="http://www.pawm.ca/2011/12/negotiating-surface-rights/" rel="bookmark">Negotiating Surface Rights</a></h1>
			
						<div class="entry-meta">
				<span class="sep">Posted on </span><a href="http://www.pawm.ca/2011/12/negotiating-surface-rights/" title="1:07 pm" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date" datetime="2011-12-17T13:07:28+00:00">December 17, 2011</time></a><span class="by-author"> <span class="sep"> by </span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://www.pawm.ca/author/sean/" title="View all posts by Sean" rel="author">Sean</a></span></span>			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
			
						<div class="comments-link">
				<a href="http://www.pawm.ca/2011/12/negotiating-surface-rights/#respond"><span class="leave-reply">Reply</span></a>			</div>
					</header><!-- .entry-header -->

				<div class="entry-content">
			<p>From the Agriculture and Rural Development site:</p>
<blockquote><p>This pamphlet provides basic information for landowners and occupants who are involved in negotiations related to surface rights. Negotiating a surface rights agreement can involve many aspects that are specific to your own situation. This pamphlet gives an overview of a complex topic. If you have questions about surface rights agreements, please call the Farmers’ Advocate office at 310-FARM (3276).</p></blockquote>
<p>You can view the original page <a href="http://www1.agric.gov.ab.ca/$department/deptdocs.nsf/all/agdex1126">here</a>. You can download the pamphlet in PDF format by clicking <a href="http://www1.agric.gov.ab.ca/$department/deptdocs.nsf/all/agdex1126/$file/878-1.pdf?OpenElement">this link</a>.</p>
					</div><!-- .entry-content -->
		
